Commentary Text: Rahul Tewatia to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Buttler!! Good move by Smith to stick with Rahul Tewatia. He was hit for two boundaries in the first over, but the RR skipper had faith and gets the much-needed reward. There's something about this lad, he has a knack of picking wickets with the ball. Goes for the wrong 'un and made sure there's no room for Gill to fetch and to compound matters for KKR, Gill had to target the longer side. Opts to slogsweep and skews it off the thick inside half, only to offer catching practice for Buttler at deep mid-wicket. Shubman Gill c Buttler b Rahul Tewatia 36(24) [4s-6]

Commentary Text: Jofra Archer to Nitish Rana, out Caught by Samson!! Gone first ball. How often Jofra Archer does this for RR? Absolutely brilliant. Oh hang on! We have a review for caught behind, it's been given out onfield. Fair delivery and there seems to be some sound as the ball passed the bat. UltraEdge shows a tiny spike as the ball's close to bat it's a goner. No more reviews for KKR. Jofra Archer hits the deck hard and gets the ball to bounce and wobble away in the corridor of uncertainty, Nitish Rana was hanging on the back foot and his ungainly poke ensured it was feather of an edge to the keeper. He did consult his partner about the review, but it was a waste a review when bat was the only thing close to the ball. Nitish Rana c Samson b Jofra Archer 0(1)

Commentary Text: Chakravarthy to Buttler, out Caught by Cummins!! That's officially the game for KKR I reckon. Not that they weren't bossing the game already but this could perhaps be that final nail. Was a skiddy half-tracker from Chakravarthy, Buttler sat back for the pull over deep mid-wicket. Commentary Text: Cummins to Stokes, out Caught by Karthik!! Oh Dinesh Karthik Remember the flying catch he took in the cordon to dismiss Graeme Smith in the 2007 World T20? This one's quite up there! Ben Stokes stands in disbelief. This is a keeper's wicket. So Cummins angled the full ball in, was in the arc for Stokes to tee off, Stokes went but got a thick edge. Would have been a regulation catch for first slip if there was one, DK flew full length to his left and caught this left-handed behind him. This is the sort of stuff that can really lift a team. And it's the in-form Ben Stokes too! Stokes c Karthik b Cummins 18(11) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Cummins to Uthappa, out Caught by K Nagarkoti!! Robin Uthappa, what have you done! Cummins has just bowled the most expensive opening over of the season and you've flicked a ball straight to the lone fielder on the leg-side fence. Uthappa thought he will flick this towards mid-wicket and didn't bother to keep it down because he always wanted to clear the infield, unfortunately for him he hit it squarer and the fielder moved to his left to take a tumbling catch. This is the sort of luck you need going your way in a big game with a poor opening over. Uthappa c K Nagarkoti b Cummins 6(2) [6s-1]
